with the rise of the gay rights movement in recent years has been an increasing focus on the biblical statements regarding homosexuality or As part of this focus the meaning of the term arsenokoitai used twice by the apostle Paul Cor I Tim has received vigorous This issue is particularly crucial to contemporary society since so much of modern ethics is shaped by biblical More particularly the concern over gay rights and the place of gays or homosexuals in the church and in society require the resolution of biblical This study of historical linguistic and literary matters will survey and evalutate recent proposals for the meaning of arsenokoitai and present evidence to point to a Several writers and their positions represent the modern debate on this Three authors Bailey Boswell and Scroggs have provoked considerable discussion and significantly encouraged the wider acceptance of the homosexual lifestyle in society in the church and in the Footnotes For convenience sake the term homosexual is used to encompass both same sex orientation and same sex The meaning of this term is one of the main considerations of this These times are differnt from just over a century Then P Fairbairn Pastoral Epistles Edinburg could write of arsenokoitai thit it is a term for which fortunately our language has no proper Unknowingly he thereby touched upon the basis for the contemporary debate and THe present writer endorses the Pauline authorship of the Pastoral Epistles on the basis of internal and external evidence see Donald Guthrie New Testament Introduction ed for an extensive discussion and citation of supporters of the Pauline authorship For example see Scroggs' influence on Olson Untangling the Web The Other Side April For a study suggesting a further prohibition of homosexuality in the OT see Phillips Unconvering the Father's Skirt VT Jan For a bibliography of other sources dealing with arsenokoitai see the Wisondisc Religion Indexes NY Wison